actions and communication patterns within the family system\",16\r\n885,THERAPIST,FIRST INTERVIEW,Therapists conduct the first interview to assess the client's issues and determine the suitability of the therapeutic relationship,16\r\n886,THERAPIST,SECOND INTERVIEW,Therapists conduct the second interview to explore the client's issues in more detail and establish a treatment plan,16\r\n193,BEHAVIORAL THERAPY,EXPOSURE THERAPY,Exposure therapy is a technique used in behavioral therapy,15\r\n812,BEHAVIOR THERAPY,PSYCHOTHERAPIST,Psychotherapists are one of the types of professionals who can be trained to conduct behavior therapy.,15\r\n804,BEHAVIOR THERAPY,COGNITIVE BEHAVIOR THERAPY,\"Behavior Therapy is a broad therapeutic approach that primarily focuses on modifying maladaptive behaviors through various techniques and interventions. Cognitive Behavior Therapy (CBT) is a specialized branch and an evolution of Behavior Therapy. While Behavior Therapy emphasizes changing behaviors directly, CBT integrates the modification of thought patterns to influence behavior. Specifically, CBT seeks to identify and alter negative or distorted thinking patterns, which in turn can lead to changes in emotional responses and behaviors. Thus, CBT builds upon the foundational principles of Behavior Therapy by incorporating cognitive processes into the therapeutic framework. Together, these approaches represent a continuum of psychological interventions aimed at improving mental health and well-being.\",14\r\n813,BEHAVIOR THERAPY,CLINICAL SOCIAL WORKER,Clinical social workers are one of the types of professionals who can be trained to conduct behavior therapy.,14\r\n815,BEHAVIOR THERAPY,BEHAVIOR THERAPIST,\"Behavior therapists are trained professionals who specialize in behavior therapy techniques. They are skilled in conducting behavior therapy sessions and apply these techniques to assist clients in addressing various behavioral issues. Their expertise lies in utilizing behavior therapy 